{"key":"processedPost-27928665","value":{"id":27928665,"first":27927928,"last":27984905,"when":1662041346,"utime":"09/01/22 05:09 PM","content":"It's best to always test a new drum sterilizer with an air compressor before using steam.<br /><br />It's also best to never exceed 1 to at most 2 psi.&nbsp; As said above, you've created a bomb by having a sealed drum.&nbsp; Remember, when water turns to steam, it expands by a factor of at least 1600 at atmospheric pressure.&nbsp; Add some pressure and it's even greater if a rip occurs in the drum.<br /><br />I'd open up that relief valve so it's always open during use. This will allow steam to constantly escape.&nbsp; Adjust the burner so only a small amount escapes after the first hour or so.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pressure Barrel","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}